f=Executive Office/echo/operational/agent/echo-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration echo, scoped strictly what echo's skills actually reference. Unlike marcus, echo escalation-threshold tie-break-routing need anywhere skills file deliberately smaller, copy marcus's shape. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Metrics --- \· metrics_source: <FILL_IN>       # where echo pulls company metrics from (dashboard URL, file path, connector \· # name, etc.) — referenced by both pitch-narrative (Phase 1) and \· # investor-update-template (Phase 1). One shared source, not asked per-run \· # once this is filled in.` · in=Until `metrics_source` filled in, pitch-narrative investor-update-template keep asking operator per-run rather assuming source that's skill's documented fallback behavior, unchanged file existing. Until `approval_contact` filled in, investor-update-template defaults asking operator directly before send (its stated fallback). Until `send_channel` filled in, investor-update-template produces final update file/draft hands operator send manually (its stated fallback). echo's skill set grows something new needs configuring, add rather inventing new shape don't add fields speculatively; add what skill actually references. · f=file existing doesn't change any skill's fallback behavior gives skills something concrete check first. empty/unfilled config equivalent config existing all.